				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 06 Jun 2018 09:29:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Mortos</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1705184</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is nice. It's all very low key, which I appreciate, and you leave the right amount of unknowns at the end to hold interest. Your interview could use a few tweaks to make it a little easier to read and more visually appealing (for example, picking a name for the researcher and losing the blackboxes, and reducing the number of ellipsis you use, especially at the start of sentences), but that isn't a dealbreaker. +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
